, guidance and internal policies and procedures \u2022 Provide support to managers on compliance matters \u2022 Engage with third party compliance auditors \u2022 Keep up to date with the latest cryptocurrency regulatory requirements in the UK. Candidate Requirements \u2022 A minimum of 3 years\u2019 experience in a compliance function within a Fintech Company, with knowledge of financial services laws and experience of the regulatory requirements within FCA Handbook and other relevant regulatory bodies \u2022 Experience in a fast paced operations centre environment: compliance monitoring, oversight, reporting and MI analytics \u2022 Recent experience of drafting and reviewing compliance policies and standard operating procedures \u2022 Execution-focused, with intellectual strength and the flexibility to quickly metabolise complex issues and provide workable solutions \u2022 Excellent communication and influencing skills, with the ability to deal with complex issues and projects whilst managing multiple (and potentially conflicting) stakeholder requirements and teams in numerous jurisdictions \u2022 High energy levels and ability to work under pressure to meet deadlines \u2022 Relevant industry qualifications, including QFA, ACOI, and ICA \u2022 Flexible and adaptable style with good critical thinking and analytical skills Please note, all applicants must be eligible to work in the UK. Skills Compliance, Moitoring, MI Analytics Compensation Competitive Applications for this job are currently closed. Apply on CryptoJobs Related jobs you might like Compliance Office/Manager Huobi Singapore Full Time Tech Singapore 859 views \u00c2\u00b7 posted 125 days ago Chief Technical Officer Black Pay Full Time Tech Remote Washington D.C. 1411 views \u00c2\u00b7 posted 192 days ago Social media marketing PR Officer Genesis Mining Full Time Tech Remote 1939 views \u00c2\u00b7 posted 357 days ago Chief Operating Officer Maxfield Search Full Time Tech London 1831 views \u00c2\u00b7 